(245, 1, '2020-08-05 16:13:48', '2020-08-05 16:13:48', '<p>Canadian architecture firm Atelier Schwimmer has contrasted planks of charred wood with pale wood to form a cabin for brothers overlooking a lake in Canada.</p><p>Chalet Lakeside is located on a wooded site that faces Lake Brome in a small town east of Montreal.</p><p>Atelier Schwimmer constructed the 3,200-square-foot (297-square-metre) cabin for two siblings who enjoy outdoor activities and wanted a place to escape city life.</p><p>The residence comprises a single rectangular volume with a gabled roofline and recessed walls. For the cladding, the studio charred larch wood, while the set back portions are left exposed and treated with a natural oil.</p><p>\"This play of dark and light increases the singular aspect of the house,\" the studio said.</p><p>Large glass sliding doors and a wood deck wrap around a back corner of the cabin. Windows and doors on all sides are oriented to face the grassy property, dock and lake.</p><p>Inside, a portion of the ceiling is cut away to give height to the open-plan living space. The design in the space revolves around a concrete fireplace in the centre of the room.</p><p>Logs are inserted inside a glass box within a void cut into the centre of the monolithic volume.</p><p>\"The design was developed around a fireplace set beside a triple-height area that makes it visible from everywhere within the cabin thus generating a canyon of hospitality,\" it added.</p><p>Concrete covers the floors and the walls, while the ceilings are panelled with pale wood planks. An L-shaped plywood bench forms a seating area against a window with a lake view.</p><p>Attached to the ceiling is a climbing rope that extends from the peak of the gabled roof down onto the living room floor.</p><p>Wood steps form the staircase that leads to the upper level, where the four bedrooms and a family room are located. Three rectangular skylights above the stair landing brighten the hallway that is open to the lower level.</p><p>Other projects overlooking lakes in Canada include a charred cedar residence and boathouse anchored on a wood deck and a black house in Quebec with a terrace that extends over the water.</p>		\n			<figure class=\'gallery-item\'>\n				<a data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"dibq3xx\" data-elementor-lightbox-title=\"chalet-lakeside-atelier-schwimmer-canada_dezeen_2364_col_10-scaled\" href=\'http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/chalet-lakeside-atelier-schwimmer-canada_dezeen_2364_col_10-scaled-1.jpg\'><img width=\"768\" height=\"1152\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/chalet-lakeside-atelier-schwimmer-canada_dezeen_2364_col_10-scaled-1-768x1152.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/chalet-lakeside-atelier-schwimmer-canada_dezeen_2364_col_10-scaled-1-768x1152.jpg 768w, http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/chalet-lakeside-atelier-schwimmer-canada_dezeen_2364_col_10-scaled-1-200x300.jpg 200w, http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/chalet-lakeside-atelier-schwimmer-canada_dezeen_2364_col_10-scaled-1-683x1024.jpg 683w, http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/chalet-lakeside-atelier-schwimmer-canada_dezeen_2364_col_10-scaled-1-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/chalet-lakeside-atelier-schwimmer-canada_dezeen_2364_col_10-scaled-1-1366x2048.jpg 1366w, http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/chalet-lakeside-atelier-schwimmer-canada_dezeen_2364_col_10-scaled-1.jpg 1707w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" /></a>\n			</figure><figure class=\'gallery-item\'>\n				<a data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"dibq3xx\" data-elementor-lightbox-title=\"chalet-lakeside-atelier-schwimmer-canada_dezeen_2364_col_3-scaled\" href=\'http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/chalet-lakeside-atelier-schwimme